# WHAT IT IS
#   yearprogress is a tiny single-purpose Mastodon bot — invoke
#   it on a cron schedule and it posts a typed Status to the
#   configured Mastodon-compatible server containing a progress
#   bar + percentage showing how far along the calendar year we
#   are.  Typical output:
#
#       ▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓░░░░░░░░░░░░ 41 %
#
#   Server URL and bearer token can be set via CLI flags
#   (`-s/--server`, `-t/--token`), via a config file
#   (`-c/--config`), or interactively on first run (the bot
#   prompts and then writes the config to the standard XDG
#   config directory).  `-d/--dry-run` short-circuits the
#   actual `client.v1.statuses.create({status})` HTTP call —
#   useful for testing the rendered bar without spamming the
#   timeline.  `-f/--force` overrides the once-per-day guard
#   and posts even when the percentage hasn't changed since
#   the last invocation.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from packages/mastodon-bot-
#                       yearprogress/src/cli.ts commander.js
#                       chain; extracted via `gh api repos/
#                       ffflorian/node-packages/contents/
#                       packages/mastodon-bot-yearprogress/
#                       src/cli.ts`)
#
#   yearprogress [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -s, --server <HOST>            Specify a Mastodon server
#                                    (e.g. https://mastodon.social
#                                    or any Pleroma / Akkoma /
#                                    Iceshrimp / Firefish
#                                    instance — `masto` speaks
#                                    the standard Mastodon REST
#                                    API across all of them)
#     -t, --token <TOKEN>            Specify an access token
#                                    (Bearer token issued by
#                                    the server's
#                                    /api/v1/apps/verify_
#                                    credentials endpoint)
#     -d, --dry-run                  Do not actually send data
#                                    or write the config file
#                                    (renders the toot, prints
#                                    it to stdout, exits)
#     -c, --config <FILE>            Specify a config file
#                                    (defaults to the XDG
#                                    config dir;
#                                    interactively created on
#                                    first run if absent)
#     -f, --force                    Force sending the toot
#                                    even when the year-
#                                    progress percentage
#                                    hasn't changed since the
#                                    last invocation
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Show version
